HEADWORD: Grenadillo
<hw>Gren`a*dil"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
granadillo.]</ety> <def>A handsome tropical American wood, much used for
making flutes and other wind instruments; -- called also
<altname>Grenada cocos</altname>, or <altname>cocus</altname>, and
<altname>red ebony</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grenadine</ent>⟦br⟧
